definition: to establish/to found/to set up/to build/to construct
to stand/to set up/to establish/to lay down/to draw up/at once/immediately

pinyin: jian4 li4 zheng4 shi4 wai4 jiao1 guan1 xi4

sentences.english: How can I rebuild my trust in him?
sentences.chinese: 怎樣才能重新建立起我對他的信任？

sentences.english: Adorno attempts to build real nature aesthetics.
sentences.chinese: 阿多諾力圖建立真正的自然美學。

sentences.english: You need to build a business, not to make new friends on-line.
sentences.chinese: 你需要建立一個生意，不結交新朋在網上。

sentences.english: The description of a nominal taxon when it is established.
sentences.chinese: 建立一個命名分類單元時所做的描述。

sentences.english: How could we establish multi-lingual communication models in different contexts?
sentences.chinese: 如何建立不同情境下多語言溝通模式？

sentences.english: Objective To establish a method for the determination of in Folium Cajani by HPLC.
sentences.chinese: 目的建立木豆葉中牡荊苷的含量測定方法。

sentences.english: For example, we have built a dental clinic in Swaziland, Africa.
sentences.chinese: 例如，我們已經在非洲斯威士蘭建立了一家牙科診所。

sentences.english: Is Japan Planning to Create an Anti-China"Asian NATO"?

sentences.english: It took some time to develop a central money-marking business.

sentences.english: And we used that to set up the iterated integral.
sentences.chinese: 我們還用那個來建立累次積分。

sentences.english: You could actually use a closure to do the resource setup and cleanup instead.
sentences.chinese: 實際上可以使用閉包代替該方法來建立和清除資源。

sentences.english: Unlike a changeset, a shelveset is a non-versioned entity.
sentences.chinese: 與變更集不同的是，擱置集是沒有建立版本的實體。

sentences.english: They decided that the establishment of a separate society founded on Nazi principles of genetic purity was the answer.
sentences.chinese: 這答案是建立一純正的納粹理想的亞利安社會。

sentences.english: The hall was built on a high terrace, and has 21 rooms.
sentences.chinese: 大廳既建立在一個高的平臺，並有21間。

sentences.english: Objective To verify the specificity and validity of the microbial limit tests of glycyrrhetinic acid.
sentences.chinese: 目的建立適合於甘草酸的微生物限度檢查方法。

definition: to build (esp. with simple materials)/to knock together (a temporary shed)/to rig up

to implement/to carry out/to put into practice
